1
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:32,009
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:35,030
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,789
Boyi and Shuqi would rather starve
than eat the grain of Zhou.

4
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,789
They picked ferns and ate them,

5
00:01:42,789 --> 00:01:44,789
and starved to death.

6
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:47,420
There you go again, saying things
I don't understand—

7
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:48,509
what "Shu," what "ferns"?

8
00:01:48,509 --> 00:01:49,590
What does it mean?

9
00:01:50,420 --> 00:01:52,550
Chinese patriots with lofty ideals

10
00:01:52,710 --> 00:01:54,259
keep their integrity.

11
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:58,100
They would rather go to Shouyang Mountain
and live on fiddlehead

12
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:00,160
than eat Zhou Dynasty's rice,

13
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,850
choosing death to uphold their ideals.

14
00:02:01,850 --> 00:02:03,180
Then why do I pick these fiddleheads?

15
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:04,380
It's the middle of winter—

16
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:05,760
where am I supposed
to go pick them for you?

17
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,300
Master, let me tell you,

18
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,800
if we waited to save enough money

19
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,100
to buy rice on the black market,

20
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,680
you would've starved to death long ago.

21
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,470
I'd rather starve than eat Japanese rice.

22
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:15,640
What Japanese rice or Chinese rice?

23
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:16,760
I only know

24
00:02:16,790 --> 00:02:18,840
that I bought the rice with my money.

25
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:21,440
I got it with my life.

26
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:22,190
I only know

27
00:02:22,190 --> 00:02:23,850
that people must live and eat.

28
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:25,630
Only when you eat this rice

29
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:26,750
will it taste good.

30
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:29,560
Fine, if you don't eat, I will.

31
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:40,970
Yummy.

32
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:42,090
Look at you.

33
00:02:42,710 --> 00:02:44,640
Look at the way you eat.

34
00:02:44,730 --> 00:02:47,640
Shameless and ignorant.

35
00:02:47,660 --> 00:02:49,079
A pair of chopsticks and a mouth.

36
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:50,810
What's wrong with the way I eat?

37
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:51,860
You eat so elegantly.

38
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:52,730
Come on, eat one.

39
00:02:52,730 --> 00:02:53,920
Let me see you eat one.

40
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:56,120
You can't talk about ice
to a summer bug,

41
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,130
nor about the sea to a frog in a well.

42
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:01,550
Why am I a bug again?

43
00:03:01,670 --> 00:03:02,400
Will I always be a bug

44
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,740
in your eyes?

45
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:05,280
Master, let me tell you,

46
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,420
this "bug" is the one

47
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:08,360
who brought your family to the concession.

48
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,190
This "bug" is the one

49
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:11,260
who took you out of the shelter.

50
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,400
It's because of this "bug"

51
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,110
that Zhang Yunqi and his wife
don't dare bully you,

52
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:16,170
and you get to stand here scolding me.

53
00:03:16,410 --> 00:03:17,840
Sure, you've got lofty principles—

54
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,170
you're good at talking.

55
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:19,810
By the way,

56
00:03:20,079 --> 00:03:21,700
what about the travel money
you promised me for going to Wuhan?

57
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:22,829
Have you given it to me?

58
00:03:22,829 --> 00:03:25,020
I haven't got a penny yet.

59
00:03:25,130 --> 00:03:27,130
Well...

60
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,750
Meng Wanfu,

61
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:32,590
we will definitely pay you back.

62
00:03:32,610 --> 00:03:34,610
The Zhang family will never owe you!

63
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:35,850
All right.

64
00:03:35,850 --> 00:03:37,300
I can't explain it to you.

65
00:03:37,329 --> 00:03:38,670
But I can tell you this.

66
00:03:38,850 --> 00:03:40,120
I, Zhang Ruxian,

67
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:42,270
will never eat Japanese rice!

68
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:44,829
Yujiao won't,

69
00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:46,390
nor will Yueming.

70
00:03:46,810 --> 00:03:49,579
Stay out of the Zhang family's
business from now on.

71
00:03:49,579 --> 00:03:51,780
If we starve, that's our own problem.

72
00:03:51,810 --> 00:03:53,160
You old...

73
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:56,850
I can't explain it to you either.

74
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:58,960
Eat it or not.

75
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:02,950
Wanfu.

76
00:04:05,170 --> 00:04:06,130
I'm not angry.

77
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:08,660
I don't care to argue with him.

78
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,409
Father, I'm coming in.

79
00:04:57,570 --> 00:04:59,890
Father, are you hungry?

80
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,560
I reheated the dishes.

81
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,090
Come and have a bite.

82
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:06,580
I can't eat anymore.

83
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,600
We don't eat rice.

84
00:05:13,790 --> 00:05:14,920
We eat steamed buns.

85
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:16,670
I made them with corn starch.

86
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,430
Don't worry.

87
00:05:17,690 --> 00:05:18,970
I kneaded the dough for a long time

88
00:05:18,970 --> 00:05:20,680
and picked out all the dirt

89
00:05:20,710 --> 00:05:22,030
and little stones.

90
00:05:43,659 --> 00:05:44,860
Father,

91
00:05:45,710 --> 00:05:47,630
are you still mad at Wanfu?

92
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:51,770
Yujiao,

93
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:56,040
I might be

94
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,730
a pedantic

95
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:02,240
and stubborn old fool

96
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,750
in some people's eyes.

97
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:09,660
But a person must have integrity.

98
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:12,250
I would rather die

99
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,820
than submit to the Japanese.

100
00:06:15,470 --> 00:06:16,300
Yes,

101
00:06:17,690 --> 00:06:19,160
you're right.

102
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,430
But

103
00:06:22,270 --> 00:06:23,590
Wanfu

104
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:26,410
almost lost his life

105
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:29,310
just to get us some food.

106
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:32,909
I know it all.

107
00:06:33,730 --> 00:06:34,630
I know that

108
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,680
he—

109
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:39,090
though rough around the edges

110
00:06:39,210 --> 00:06:40,870
and a bit slick with his words—

111
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,630
is not a bad person at heart.

112
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,630
He's quite kind.

113
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:49,630
I was just angry for a moment

114
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:51,200
and spoke too harshly.

115
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:53,280
I spoke too harshly.

116
00:06:55,630 --> 00:06:56,670
It's all my fault

117
00:06:56,960 --> 00:07:00,150
for losing the money and the land deed,

118
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:03,120
bringing us to this state.

119
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,280
Yujiao,

120
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:08,460
I've made you and Yueming suffer.

121
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,770
How can you blame yourself?

122
00:07:11,390 --> 00:07:13,190
Besides, look at me and Yueming,

123
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,480
we are doing fine.

124
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,830
Go close the door.

125
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:23,490
Go quickly.

126
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:41,820
Look,

127
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:44,690
this "A Record of Mount Lu"

128
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:47,210
is a printed edition
from the Southern Song Dynasty.

129
00:07:47,210 --> 00:07:49,390
[A Record of Mount Lu]

130
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,770
It is rare in the world now,

131
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:51,020
and it is my

132
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:53,950
last treasure.

133
00:07:55,990 --> 00:07:59,310
[A Record of Mount Lu]

134
00:07:57,190 --> 00:07:58,670
Take it and sell it.

135
00:07:58,850 --> 00:08:00,450
Put it back quickly.

136
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,500
How can you sell it?

137
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,420
It's your life.

138
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:05,450
But you and Yuelin
need to live a good life—

139
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:07,370
that's what matters most to me.

140
00:08:08,470 --> 00:08:10,080
As for Yunqi and his wife,

141
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,520
I've already seen through them.

142
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:14,720
But no matter how hard life is,

143
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,530
we still have to grit our teeth
and get through it.

144
00:08:18,470 --> 00:08:21,090
These hard days
won't just last a day or two.

145
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:22,780
It may be a long struggle,

146
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:24,300
and it may only get harder

147
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,310
and harder.

148
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:28,680
Tell me, what's the use

149
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:30,910
of keeping these worldly possessions?

150
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:33,480
Find someone capable,

151
00:08:33,549 --> 00:08:35,270
who understands and cherishes it,

152
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:36,630
and entrust it to him.

153
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:40,039
Protect it through these troubled times

154
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,370
so it can be passed down.

155
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:42,720
On one hand,

156
00:08:42,940 --> 00:08:45,490
it preserves something
for Chinese culture.

157
00:08:45,580 --> 00:08:46,310
On the other,

158
00:08:46,450 --> 00:08:48,830
it helps us survive this crisis.

159
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:51,360
Isn't that the best of both worlds?

160
00:08:54,090 --> 00:08:58,100
[A Record of Mount Lu]

161
00:08:58,890 --> 00:08:59,490
Father,

162
00:09:03,490 --> 00:09:04,730
who was it

163
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:07,450
that treated this book like a treasure,

164
00:09:07,450 --> 00:09:09,050
holding it close to his chest

165
00:09:09,390 --> 00:09:11,450
all the way from Nanjing to Shanghai?

166
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:13,510
And who,

167
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:15,590
through so many hardships,

168
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:17,920
still managed to

169
00:09:17,950 --> 00:09:19,900
keep this book safely here?

170
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:24,400
I think

171
00:09:25,830 --> 00:09:28,030
you are the one who understands it best.

172
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:32,580
Yujiao, Yujiao,

173
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:35,500
times are just too hard right now.

174
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,310
It's too hard.

175
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,080
Yujiao.

176
00:09:43,710 --> 00:09:46,260
Dad, keep the key safe.

177
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:48,670
Make sure no one finds it.

178
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:51,890
That's true.

179
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:53,340
Let's eat.

180
00:09:58,890 --> 00:10:00,320
I'm perfectly capable.

181
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:02,410
I'll find a job sooner or later.

182
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:05,900
Besides, supporting you
and taking care of Yueming

183
00:10:05,930 --> 00:10:08,080
is what I should be doing anyway.

184
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,820
You have to have faith in me.

185
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:10,500
Right?

186
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,960
I do.

187
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,050
I believe you.

188
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:40,520
I kneaded it pretty well, didn't I?

189
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:43,070
It's delicious,

190
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:45,540
chewy,

191
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,640
and filling.

192
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:58,510
Father, soak it in water.

193
00:10:58,510 --> 00:11:00,570
Let it soak for a while before you eat.

194
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:08,200
Has Yueming eaten?

195
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,910
He's already eaten.

196
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:26,620
[Street promoters wanted (men and women)]

197
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:31,770
[Publication Salespeople Wanted]
[Typist Wanted]

198
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:37,060
[Publication Salespeople Wanted]

199
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:43,300
[Jasmine Café]

200
00:12:57,020 --> 00:13:00,860
[Taikang Company]

201
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,390
Eat slowly; don't choke.

202
00:13:09,860 --> 00:13:12,680
[Desserts, Pudding, Cakes]

203
00:13:17,010 --> 00:13:17,850
Excuse me.

204
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:27,670
[Desserts, Pudding, Cakes]

205
00:13:27,670 --> 00:13:33,940
[Litana Patisserie]

206
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,240
Cigarettes!

207
00:13:32,740 --> 00:13:34,870
Would you like some cigarettes, miss?

208
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,960
Why is this blood draw taking so long?

209
00:14:18,030 --> 00:14:21,720
[Brown sugar water]

210
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,190
My grandpa said

211
00:14:29,290 --> 00:14:31,020
blood is the vessel of the soul.

212
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:32,400
If all the blood drains away,

213
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:33,490
the soul will be gone too.

214
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:35,110
Just look at these fingernails.

215
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:36,170
If they turn white,

216
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:37,800
the soul has left.

217
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:40,920
They really are white.

218
00:14:42,810 --> 00:14:44,640
Baked sweet potatoes!

219
00:14:45,950 --> 00:14:47,740
Baked sweet potatoes!

220
00:14:54,490 --> 00:14:56,440
Baked sweet potatoes!

221
00:14:54,670 --> 00:14:59,190
[Pu-Chi Hospital]

222
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,630
Kid,

223
00:15:07,650 --> 00:15:08,440
it's so cold out.

224
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,900
Why are you out here alone?

225
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:13,710
I like being outside.

226
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:15,000
Why?

227
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:16,310
Why don't you go home?

228
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:21,290
It's colder at home than it is here.

229
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:24,640
[Zeng Xuefei, Underground
Communist Party member]

230
00:15:30,310 --> 00:15:31,540
How much for these two?

231
00:15:31,540 --> 00:15:32,300
Four cents.

232
00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:33,330
Okay.

233
00:15:34,860 --> 00:15:35,660
Exact change.

234
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:37,930
Thank you.

235
00:15:38,260 --> 00:15:38,940
Here.

236
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:41,830
Take it.

237
00:15:42,470 --> 00:15:43,740
Warm yourself up.

238
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,100
Does it smell good?

239
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,130
Thank you.

240
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,480
Hurry home.

241
00:15:59,130 --> 00:16:00,910
Hello, we are from the Red Cross.

242
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:02,410
We sincerely ask patriots to donate blood.

243
00:16:02,410 --> 00:16:04,210
Hello, we are from the Red Cross.

244
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:07,730
[Liangxin Blood Donation Center]

245
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:06,330
Hello, we are from the Red Cross.

246
00:16:06,350 --> 00:16:08,040
We sincerely ask patriots to donate blood.

247
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,550
Hello, we are from the Red Cross.

248
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:10,920
We sincerely ask patriots to donate blood.

249
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:12,050
Please take a look.

250
00:16:12,150 --> 00:16:13,000
Donate blood?

251
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:13,750
Yes.

252
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,930
For the suffering Chinese people.

253
00:16:15,950 --> 00:16:17,010
Please take a look.

254
00:16:17,110 --> 00:16:18,230
Where can I donate?

255
00:16:18,260 --> 00:16:19,740
Turn left at the hospital lobby ahead.

256
00:16:18,530 --> 00:16:21,150
[Liangxin Blood Donation Center]

257
00:16:19,870 --> 00:16:21,350
There is a room with a red cross;

258
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:22,390
that's the place.

259
00:16:22,510 --> 00:16:23,780
Okay, I'll go donate.

260
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,610
Thank you, sir.

261
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:26,480
Thank you.

262
00:16:27,790 --> 00:16:28,950
Thank you, sir.

263
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:30,440
Come, take a look, everyone.

264
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,760
Please lend a helping hand

265
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:33,570
and help our compatriots.

266
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:37,440
[Liangxin Blood Donation Center]

267
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:37,230
What are you doing?

268
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:38,010
Put this away.

269
00:16:38,010 --> 00:16:39,020
Don't promote here.

270
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:40,710
-Are you out of your mind?
-The soldiers on the front line

271
00:16:40,710 --> 00:16:42,990
- are fighting and bleeding for us
on the battlefield.
-Blood is our own blood.

272
00:16:42,590 --> 00:16:45,000
[Liangxin Blood Donation Center]

273
00:16:43,020 --> 00:16:45,440
-The Chinese help our compatriots.
-The money we earn is for ourselves—

274
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:48,000
-Save our fellow Chinese people.
-why should we just give it away?

275
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,600
Thank you, everyone.

276
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:51,290
-Please help us.
-Think about

277
00:16:51,290 --> 00:16:52,820
-Please help us Chinese.
-the days of going hungry…

278
00:16:52,730 --> 00:16:56,570
[Pu-Chi Hospital]

279
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,830
-Thank you.
-Think about your parents.

280
00:16:54,830 --> 00:16:56,230
They're waiting for you at home.

281
00:16:56,230 --> 00:16:57,460
Do you want money?

282
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:59,940
[Quiet Please]

283
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:02,760
[Quiet Please]

284
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:02,990
Ma'am, are you here to donate blood?

285
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:06,000
May I ask where the donated blood
will be used?

286
00:17:06,829 --> 00:17:07,400
Ma'am,

287
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,700
blood must be dedicated to patriots.

288
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:10,920
We will issue you

289
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,790
a Red Cross blood donation certificate.

290
00:17:12,790 --> 00:17:14,930
I can't say any more.

291
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,839
The blood is for the frontline soldiers.

292
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:18,040
Soldiers from where?

293
00:17:18,190 --> 00:17:19,710
Guerrillas around Shanghai,

294
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:20,970
and severely wounded soldiers

295
00:17:20,970 --> 00:17:23,690
sent from the Xuzhou battlefield
and other battlefields.

296
00:17:23,690 --> 00:17:25,319
If you can guarantee

297
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:26,270
that the donated blood

298
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:28,690
will definitely be used
on the frontline soldiers,

299
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:29,950
then I am willing to donate.

300
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:31,190
I can guarantee it.

301
00:17:40,510 --> 00:17:41,510
Here's the thing,

302
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:42,730
in the concession,

303
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,840
anti-Japanese activities cannot be public.

304
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,700
Traitors and spies are everywhere.

305
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:48,460
We have to be on guard.

306
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,450
We can only promote

307
00:17:49,450 --> 00:17:51,510
under the guise of helping refugees.

308
00:17:51,780 --> 00:17:53,880
But the people of Shanghai know us.

309
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:56,040
They know it perfectly well.

310
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,420
So every day,

311
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:59,610
there are still many people
coming to donate blood.

312
00:17:59,610 --> 00:18:00,690
Then I understand.

313
00:18:00,850 --> 00:18:01,530
Thank you.

314
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:02,510
Don't worry.

315
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,290
What's your name, please?

316
00:18:14,330 --> 00:18:15,290
Ding Yujiao.

317
00:18:15,310 --> 00:18:16,570
Do you know your blood type?

318
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:17,040
Type A.

319
00:18:17,070 --> 00:18:18,100
Okay.

320
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,030
Come.

321
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:41,820
Please clench your fist.

322
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:57,380
[Xuzhou—Northwest Army Army Barracks]

323
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,010
It hurts so much!

324
00:19:08,850 --> 00:19:10,410
Throw me gently.

325
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:16,840
Is your matter hopeless?

326
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:17,750
There is hope.

327
00:19:18,110 --> 00:19:19,770
Why didn't you say so earlier?

328
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:22,240
Can you be reinstated?

329
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,650
It's hard to explain in a few words.

330
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:25,820
We have to wait.

331
00:19:27,710 --> 00:19:29,040
As long as there is hope.

332
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,420
Then why did you come back to find me

333
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:33,220
and continue to be my counselor?

334
00:19:38,150 --> 00:19:39,210
About this,

335
00:19:39,690 --> 00:19:41,790
we have to talk to them.

336
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:44,370
They beat us up just now,

337
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:45,740
and tied us up now.

338
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,220
Who knows what will happen next.

339
00:19:48,330 --> 00:19:49,530
Logically speaking,

340
00:19:50,550 --> 00:19:53,070
our officer should have come to
claim us long ago,

341
00:19:53,070 --> 00:19:54,870
and take us back for punishment.

342
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:57,900
It's been two days.

343
00:19:57,920 --> 00:20:00,590
They want money to let us go.

344
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,950
Our Sichuan Army is dirt poor.

345
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:04,240
We can't afford it.

346
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,410
If they really get desperate,

347
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:08,160
they won't do anything crazy, right?

348
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:09,080
Not likely.

349
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:12,310
It's just a few
old cotton coats and quilts.

350
00:20:12,340 --> 00:20:15,590
If they say it is, then it is.

351
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:16,380
Brother,

352
00:20:16,870 --> 00:20:18,730
they won't execute us, will they?

353
00:20:19,150 --> 00:20:20,550
That's really unlikely.

354
00:20:20,550 --> 00:20:21,670
They can't spare the bullets.

355
00:20:21,670 --> 00:20:22,950
They lack bullets.

356
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:25,100
They'd have to use a sword.

357
00:20:26,130 --> 00:20:27,440
Not likely.

358
00:20:31,620 --> 00:20:33,950
Every unit is short of soldiers right now.

359
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:36,310
Especially wily old soldiers like you.

360
00:20:37,540 --> 00:20:41,160
And they lack
experienced staff officers like you.

361
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:47,830
I've been riding horses for so many years,

362
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:50,830
but this is the first time
I've seen it from this angle.

363
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,440
Regimental Commander!

364
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,290
What's the situation?

365
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,530
Regimental Commander Fang
of the Sichuan Army said

366
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:24,910
we can punish them as we see fit,

367
00:21:24,910 --> 00:21:26,680
and when we're done, return them to him,

368
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,070
and he'll punish them doubly.

369
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:28,920
Return my ass.

370
00:21:29,090 --> 00:21:31,260
Stealing and robbing
strategic supplies during wartime

371
00:21:31,260 --> 00:21:32,170
is punishable by death.

372
00:21:32,170 --> 00:21:34,140
That's exactly what I told them.

373
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:38,110
But Regimental Commander Fang
said we are allied forces cooperating.

374
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,020
If we execute them,

375
00:21:39,020 --> 00:21:40,510
it won't do anyone any good.

376
00:21:40,510 --> 00:21:42,110
I said your men

377
00:21:42,130 --> 00:21:43,990
stole dozens of our rifles,

378
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:45,750
along with cotton uniforms
and food supplies—

379
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,130
altogether worth about 1,000
silver dollars.

380
00:21:47,130 --> 00:21:48,640
I'm demanding double compensation

381
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:49,790
plus ransom for the prisoners.

382
00:21:49,790 --> 00:21:51,990
I wanted 3,000 silver dollars from him.

383
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,410
Regimental Commander.

384
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:57,020
[116th Brigade, 39th Division, 40th Army]

385
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:57,040
Are you afraid the Japanese won't know
I'm the Regimental Commander?

386
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:59,040
[Pang Zhonghao, Regimental Commander
of 231st Regiment]

387
00:21:57,340 --> 00:21:58,790
No saluting in the trenches.

388
00:21:58,790 --> 00:21:59,370
Get to work.

389
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:00,170
Yes, sir.

390
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,650
What did they say?

391
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:04,920
That old fox actually knows his numbers.

392
00:22:05,510 --> 00:22:07,850
He said a new recruit is
worth 12 silver dollars,

393
00:22:07,850 --> 00:22:09,270
a veteran 20,

394
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:11,680
and even the highest-ranking one,
a platoon leader,

395
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,780
all added up still wouldn't
exceed 200 in value.

396
00:22:13,780 --> 00:22:15,510
When I heard that, I got angry.

397
00:22:15,540 --> 00:22:17,480
I said if you dare not compensate,

398
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,190
we'll take this matter

399
00:22:19,190 --> 00:22:21,030
to the headquarters of the 41st Army.

400
00:22:21,030 --> 00:22:22,550
You, the commander, have no shame.

401
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:25,210
Let's see if the Division Commander
and Army Commander of your Sichuan Army

402
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:26,070
have any shame.

403
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,650
What do you think he said in the end?

404
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:30,610
He said 400 silver dollars as a package
for compensation and apology.

405
00:22:30,610 --> 00:22:31,810
That's the final offer.

406
00:22:31,810 --> 00:22:32,870
Take it or leave it.

407
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:35,570
They really have no shame.

408
00:22:37,270 --> 00:22:39,240
How are those soldiers?
Can they take a beating?

409
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:41,240
Looking at them, they seem alright.

410
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,830
We can keep them or let them go.

411
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:44,030
But Regimental Commander,

412
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:44,790
having said that,

413
00:22:44,790 --> 00:22:46,400
400 silver dollars is still money.

414
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,310
How about we...

415
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:49,490
We'll talk about it later.

416
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:54,840
Secure the front a bit more.

417
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:57,580
Clear the obstacles in front a bit more.

418
00:22:57,580 --> 00:22:58,420
Yes, sir.

419
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:11,830
This is your blood donation certificate.

420
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:12,660
Thank you.

421
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:21,990
Please bend your elbow
and press for 5 to 10 minutes.

422
00:23:21,990 --> 00:23:22,580
Don't rub it.

423
00:23:22,580 --> 00:23:23,080
Okay.

424
00:23:27,110 --> 00:23:28,090
Thank you.

425
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,170
My husband is on the frontline.

426
00:23:31,070 --> 00:23:32,330
Donating blood to them

427
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:34,080
is like donating to my husband.

428
00:23:35,110 --> 00:23:36,680
I am Zeng Xuefei.

429
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,550
I am Ding Yujiao.

430
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,560
Sit down and rest for a while.

431
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:47,010
Slow down.

432
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:48,880
Thank you.

433
00:23:53,530 --> 00:23:54,400
Ms. Zeng,

434
00:23:55,110 --> 00:23:56,330
you just said

435
00:23:56,350 --> 00:23:58,330
people in Shanghai all know you.

436
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,960
You are...

437
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,590
We are
the Anti-Japanese Support Association.

438
00:24:02,590 --> 00:24:04,350
During the Battle of Shanghai,

439
00:24:04,790 --> 00:24:07,050
it was a very large social organization.

440
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,280
I was in charge of

441
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,950
the professional women's section.

442
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:14,480
Later, Shanghai fell.

443
00:24:14,910 --> 00:24:17,040
On the surface, we disbanded,

444
00:24:17,270 --> 00:24:18,390
but in reality,

445
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:19,900
we have been doing

446
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:21,640
the anti-war work.

447
00:24:22,830 --> 00:24:25,110
No wonder I couldn't find you anywhere.

448
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:26,510
I've been looking for you for a long time.

449
00:24:26,510 --> 00:24:27,360
Why?

450
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:29,610
There is a situation

451
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:31,970
I want to ask for your help.

452
00:24:33,180 --> 00:24:34,220
Sure.

453
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:40,590
Tell me.

454
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:42,640
It's like this.

455
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,310
There is a report

456
00:24:45,750 --> 00:24:48,880
that mentions
the Anti-Japanese Support Association.

457
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:49,720
Which one?

458
00:24:50,110 --> 00:24:51,000
This one.

459
00:24:53,270 --> 00:24:55,000
Isn't this the field hospital?

460
00:24:55,590 --> 00:24:57,920
I have delivered
medicines and supplies here.

461
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:58,960
You've been there?

462
00:24:58,960 --> 00:24:59,680
Yes.

463
00:24:59,790 --> 00:25:02,200
There is a Doctor Chen in this hospital.

464
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:05,110
He used to be a doctor
at Renji Hospital.

465
00:25:05,270 --> 00:25:06,160
Later,

466
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:08,400
he went to support the field hospital.

467
00:25:08,750 --> 00:25:10,210
He happens to be my friend.

468
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,510
And I feel

469
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:15,970
the wounded man in this photo

470
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,600
looks familiar.

471
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:19,070
I feel like when the photo was taken,

472
00:25:19,070 --> 00:25:20,310
I was at the scene.

473
00:25:20,340 --> 00:25:22,450
Then please look carefully.

474
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:24,230
Do you still remember

475
00:25:24,510 --> 00:25:25,680
this sitting man?

476
00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:27,140
I seem

477
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:30,310
to have even tried to talk to him.

478
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:31,440
What did he say?

479
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:34,080
Did he say what his name was?

480
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:35,830
Is he still alive?

481
00:25:36,610 --> 00:25:38,640
Why did I remember him at the time?

482
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,830
Because the room was

483
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:42,710
filled with cries of pain.

484
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:44,740
Even though he was badly injured,

485
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:46,270
he didn't make a sound.

486
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:48,510
He is your...

487
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:51,200
He is my husband.

488
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:53,030
I came from Nanjing to Shanghai

489
00:25:53,030 --> 00:25:54,410
just to find him.

490
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:56,480
The Ministry of War said he died.

491
00:25:56,830 --> 00:25:58,790
His officer also said he died.

492
00:25:58,810 --> 00:26:00,820
All news reports said he died.

493
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:02,680
Even his orderly said he died.

494
00:26:03,140 --> 00:26:04,630
But I don't believe it.

495
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:05,880
As soon as I saw this photo,

496
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:07,790
I knew this person was him.

497
00:26:08,070 --> 00:26:09,030
They said I was mistaken,

498
00:26:09,030 --> 00:26:10,270
that he was already dead.

499
00:26:10,270 --> 00:26:10,960
But

500
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:13,170
only I can recognize his face.

501
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:14,830
I must find him.

502
00:26:17,430 --> 00:26:18,610
If I were you,

503
00:26:19,170 --> 00:26:20,750
I would do the same.

504
00:26:21,550 --> 00:26:22,410
How about this.

505
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,720
I'll figure something out for you.

506
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,840
I will go look for Dr. Chen.

507
00:26:28,590 --> 00:26:30,120
After the fall of Shanghai,

508
00:26:30,510 --> 00:26:32,270
they should be in the countryside.

509
00:26:32,270 --> 00:26:33,400
I'll go ask him

510
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,170
if he has seen your husband.

511
00:26:35,190 --> 00:26:36,030
Is that okay?

512
00:26:36,780 --> 00:26:37,780
Thank you.

513
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:40,500
Then I'll keep

514
00:26:40,550 --> 00:26:41,750
this newspaper here.

515
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:45,960
The thing is,

516
00:26:46,110 --> 00:26:48,630
there are too many wounded
rescued every day.

517
00:26:48,630 --> 00:26:50,490
Without accurate clues,

518
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:51,590
how can he be sure

519
00:26:51,590 --> 00:26:52,980
if it's your husband?

520
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:01,550
It's alright.

521
00:27:01,670 --> 00:27:03,680
Tell me your husband's

522
00:27:03,820 --> 00:27:05,090
specific details.

523
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:25,200
[No. 8 Juren Lane,
Route Ferguson—Ding Yujiao]

524
00:27:24,870 --> 00:27:26,620
This is our home address.

525
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,000
Sorry to trouble you.

526
00:27:35,620 --> 00:27:36,770
Thank you

527
00:27:37,570 --> 00:27:38,650
for trusting me.

528
00:27:38,810 --> 00:27:40,450
As soon as I have news of him,

529
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:42,410
I'll go here to find you.

530
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:52,720
[Temporary Plasma Storage Box]

531
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:20,030
Sister,

532
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:22,940
why aren't you eating
the baked sweet potato?

533
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:26,420
I want to save it for my sister.

534
00:28:31,170 --> 00:28:32,170
Yueming,

535
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:35,200
that was the first time
I met Aunt Zeng Xuefei,

536
00:28:35,500 --> 00:28:38,530
and also the first time I came into
contact with a Communist Party member.

537
00:28:38,530 --> 00:28:41,960
It turned out that national salvation
is not just an instinct,

538
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:45,720
but more about noble beliefs
and firm actions.

539
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:48,180
Later I learned that

540
00:28:48,250 --> 00:28:50,190
in the land of Southern Jiangsu
at that time,

541
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:52,860
the New Fourth Army
was using Maoshan as its heart,

542
00:28:52,860 --> 00:28:56,450
turning the sparks of guerrilla
warfare into a prairie fire.

543
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,340
And Yan'an

544
00:28:58,360 --> 00:28:59,700
was letting the Party's roots

545
00:28:59,700 --> 00:29:02,430
run deep among
hundreds of millions of people.

546
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:05,280
Those were not just numbers,

547
00:29:05,570 --> 00:29:08,980
but millions of figures like Zeng Xuefei,

548
00:29:09,010 --> 00:29:12,500
sowing new life amidst the devastation.

549
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:14,480
Yueming, you know what?

550
00:29:14,750 --> 00:29:18,140
True hope is never solitary bravery,

551
00:29:18,170 --> 00:29:21,400
but the great power forged

552
00:29:21,420 --> 00:29:23,660
by a nation in awakening.

553
00:29:28,150 --> 00:29:29,480
Regimental Commander!

554
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:33,320
Are you an officer?

555
00:29:33,350 --> 00:29:34,650
This is our Regimental Commander Pang.

556
00:29:34,650 --> 00:29:36,020
Regimental Commander Pang, right?

557
00:29:36,020 --> 00:29:37,530
We are practically family.

558
00:29:37,530 --> 00:29:38,530
My surname is You.

559
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:40,270
No, well,

560
00:29:40,310 --> 00:29:41,550
doesn't your character "Pang"

561
00:29:41,550 --> 00:29:43,200
have a "Loong" in it?

562
00:29:43,270 --> 00:29:44,530
Loong roams in the sky,

563
00:29:44,590 --> 00:29:46,510
and I roam in the water.

564
00:29:48,790 --> 00:29:51,200
